# Feature state

See also: **`error-handling.mdc`**, **`data-ownership.mdc`**, **`async-ui.mdc`**, **`offline-reconnect.mdc`**, **`api-layer.mdc`**. Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

Each **feature surface** (list page, detail panel, editor, submit flow) exposes **one derived status** — not a pile of `isLoading`, `isPending`, `isSubmitting`, `isSaving`, `isUpdating` booleans in JSX.

No XState required. Use a **small union type** and derive it in **one place** (query hook, orchestration hook, or `src/lib/<domain>/` helper).

## Core rule

**Pages render `status` — they do not combine five TanStack flags inline.**

| Layer | Owns |
| ----- | ---- |
| TanStack Query / mutations | Raw fetch/mutation flags |
| Feature hook or `getXxxStatus()` | **Single `status` union** per surface |
| Page / component | `switch (status)` or status-driven subcomponents |

## Read surfaces (lists, details)

```typescript
// src/lib/items/itemListStatus.ts
import type { Item } from "@/api/features/items/items.schema";

export type ItemListStatus =
  | "loading"
  | "error"
  | "empty"
  | "ready";

export type ItemListQuerySlice = {
  isPending: boolean;
  isError: boolean;
  data: Item[] | undefined;
};

export function getItemListStatus({
  isPending,
  isError,
  data,
}: ItemListQuerySlice): ItemListStatus {
  if (isPending) return "loading";
  if (isError) return "error";
  if (!data?.length) return "empty";
  return "ready";
}
```

```tsx
// Page — destructure the hook, then branch on status
const { data, isPending, isError, isFetching, refetch } = useItems();
const status = getItemListStatus({ isPending, isError, data });

switch (status) {
  case "loading":
    return <ItemsSkeleton />;
  case "error":
    return <ItemsError onRetry={() => void refetch()} />;
  case "empty":
    return <ItemsEmpty />;
  case "ready":
    return (
      <ItemTable
        rows={data}
        isRefreshing={isFetching}
      />
    );
}
```

**Naming:** prefer `ready` over `success` for populated reads; reserve `success` for completed **actions** (save, submit).

Aligns with `error-handling.mdc` — this rule is **how** to structure the code, not **what** to show.

## Write surfaces (forms, mutations)

Separate **read status** from **submit status**:

```typescript
export type SubmitStatus = "idle" | "submitting" | "success" | "error";

// Orchestration hook in src/api/features/items/use-submit-item.ts
export function useSubmitItem() {
  const { mutate, isPending, isSuccess, isError } = useMutation({ ... });

  const submitStatus: SubmitStatus = isPending
    ? "submitting"
    : isSuccess
      ? "success"
      : isError
        ? "error"
        : "idle";

  return { submit: mutate, submitStatus, isPending, isError };
}
```

```tsx
const { submit, submitStatus } = useSubmitItem();

<Button disabled={submitStatus === "submitting"}>
  {submitStatus === "submitting" ? "Saving…" : "Save"}
</Button>
```

Pages may also destructure **`mutate` + `isPending`** directly from a mutation hook when there is no orchestration wrapper — same aliasing rules as queries (`api-layer.mdc`).

**Do not** add `isSaving`, `isUpdating`, and `isSubmitting` as three parallel booleans — one `submitStatus` union.

Reset `success` → `idle` after toast or navigation (timer or `onSettled`) when the control must be clickable again.

## Optional: `thinking` (streaming / AI)

For streaming or long-running AI steps, extend the union in that feature only:

```typescript
export type AssistantStatus = "idle" | "thinking" | "streaming" | "error";
```

Do not add `thinking` to every CRUD screen — only where product has a visible in-progress cognition phase.

## Where derivation lives

| Approach | When |
| -------- | ---- |
| `getXxxStatus(query)` in `src/lib/<domain>/` | Reused across pages; easy to unit test |
| `select` + mapped return in query hook | Single consumer; status travels with data |
| Orchestration hook (`useSubmitX`) | Submit flows with multiple steps |

**Do not** derive status in JSX with compound conditions:

```tsx
// Bad — spaghetti
const loading = isLoading || isFetching;
const busy = isSubmitting || isSaving || isDeleting;
if (loading && !busy) ...
```

## Multiple regions on one page

Each **region** gets its own status — not one global boolean for the whole page:

```tsx
<ItemsSummary status={summaryStatus} />
<ActivityPanel status={activityStatus} />
```

## Background refresh

`isFetching` while `status === 'ready'` → pass `isRefreshing` as a **prop**, not a separate top-level status:

```tsx
case "ready":
  return <ItemTable rows={data} isRefreshing={isFetching} />;
```

## Testing

Unit-test `getXxxStatus` with table-driven Query result shapes — no render (`vitest-testing.mdc`).

## Checklist

- [ ] Query hooks are **destructured** at the call site — no `const query = useX()` branching (`api-layer.mdc`).
- [ ] **Mutation hooks** are **destructured** too — no `const save = useSaveItem()` then `.isPending` (`api-layer.mdc`).
- [ ] **Multiple hooks** on one page use aliased names for queries and mutations — `api-layer.mdc`.
- [ ] Pages avoid inline combos of `isPending` / `isLoading` / `isFetching` for branching.
- [ ] Each data surface exports or uses one read `status` union.
- [ ] Submit flows use one `submitStatus` (or named action status) — not parallel `isSaving` flags.
- [ ] `empty` / `error` / `loading` / `ready` are mutually exclusive for reads.
- [ ] Background refetch is `isRefreshing` on the ready branch, not a conflicting status.
